description:
Roles & Responsibilities
Responsibilities
To be able to work with the Project Team in project management and design issues;
Ensures project design intent and objectives are executed;
Supports project teams in design, documentation and presentation of project;
Manages contractual issues together with Contracts department;
Ensures drawings comply to authorities requirements;
Controls and manages issuances of changes and documents to ensure consistent quality;
Contribute to the Organization operational and management system;
Responsible for the overall planning, implementation and completion of projects within specified cost, time and quality;
Maintains compliance with the relevant regulatory and legislative requirements at all times;
Plays an active role in contributing to the organisation’s continuous improvement initiatives;
To conduct technical meetings with the Client, Consultants and Contractor for on-site issues and progress;
Requirements
Degree / Diploma in Interior Design or equivalent;
Minimum 8 - 10 years relevant experience in Hospitality.
Possesses strong communication and interpersonal skills to engage and manage various stakeholders;
Resourceful and has excellent planning and time management skills;
Proactive and detail-oriented;
Able to work under pressure and manage multiple projects;
Required to go on-site occasionally.
